track_notes: Park on the road-side at the locked gate. Walk the dirt road across the fields to the treed ridge. At the high point of the road turn sharp right and follow the barbed wire fence north to the summit.

The original route followed an obvious 2-track across a field to a gap in the ridge, then ascended north up the ridge.
This route deviates NW, about half way across the field, then threads through some open forest and intersects an old trail that rises steadily to within 150m of the summit. It is shorter, and a more steady ascent.
It would be OK for a mountain bike.
Cell-phone service is still available on the summit.
track_title: Shorter Route with a steady ascent
